#. <section class="sutta" id="sn17.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga"
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 38–​43. Pitusuttādichakka → pajāpati (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:0.3"
msgid "38–​43. Pitusuttādichakka"
msgstr "38–43. Father, etc."

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.244"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa "
"yogakkhemassa adhigamāya."
msgstr ""
"“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal, bitter, and harsh. They’re "
"an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary."

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.3"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.4"
msgid "‘na cāyamāyasmā pitupi hetu … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘This venerable would not tell a deliberate lie even for the sake of their "
"father. …"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.5"
msgid "(vitthāretabbaṃ) …"
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 17.37.)"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.6"
msgid "bhātupi hetu …"
msgstr "brother …"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.7"
msgid "bhaginiyāpi hetu …"
msgstr "sister …"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.8"
msgid "puttassapi hetu …"
msgstr "son …"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.9"
msgid "dhītuyāpi hetu …"
msgstr "daughter …"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.10"
msgid "pajāpatiyāpi hetu sampajānamusā bhāseyyā’ti."
msgstr "wife.’"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.11"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtaṃ "
"pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ sampajānamusā bhāsantaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But some time later I see them tell a deliberate lie because their mind is "
"overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity."

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.12"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko "
"anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya."
msgstr ""
"That’s how brutal, bitter, and harsh are possessions, honor, and popularity. "
"They’re an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary."

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.13"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.14"
msgid ""
"‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma, na ca no uppanno "
"lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let "
"them occupy our minds.’"

msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.15"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.16"
msgid "Terasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:1.17"
msgid "Catuttho vaggo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.1"
msgid "Bhindi mūlaṃ duve dhammā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.2"
msgid "pakkantaṃ ratha mātari;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.3"
msgid "Pitā bhātā ca bhaginī,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.4"
msgid "putto dhītā pajāpatīti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn17.38-43:2.5"
msgid "Lābhasakkārasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The Linked Discourses on possessions, honor, and popularity are complete."
